result.execSummary:
The defendant Starlene nmi Grant was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Neglecting a Child, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 948.21(1)(a).
  • Neglecting a Child, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 948.21(1)(a).
  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Defendant appeared with counsel SPD Paul Fredrickson.  ADA Melissa Inlow appears for the State.  ADA Inlow filed an amended Information and is recommending probation - joint recommendation.  Judge states there was never an Information filed prior to this.  Inlow then stated that it would be more appropriate to file an amended complaint as they are now misdemeanor charges.  Judge said they can proceed today and will refer to the charges in the amended Information document but an amended complaint should be filed.  Court reviews the amended charges with the defendant.  She pleads guilty to Counts 1 & 2 - Child Neglect, 948.21(1)(a) and guilty to Count 3 - Obstructing, 946.41(1).  Court reviews the elements of the 3 charges/PLQ/WOR/plea agreement.  Court finds she understands the proceedings and makes her pleas and waives her rights freely, voluntarily, and intelligently; a factual basis exists and finds her guilty of all 3 counts.  Joint recommendation of 2 years probation on each count with conditions of:    Not to enter into any bars, taverns, liquor stores, liquor department of grocery stores, the bar areas of restaurants. Defendant may not possess or consume any alcohol, nor be anywhere alcohol is available for consumption on the premises where the defendant is located.  The defendant shall comply with any treatment, evaluations and/or programming as deemed appropriate by the COMPAS assessment and the probation agent.  Defendant must sign any releases agent deems necessary to verify defendant's compliance with probation conditions.  Defendant speaks.  Court adopts the joint recommendation and withholds sentences on all 3 counts and places on 2 years probation with the following conditions:    The defendant shall comply with any treatment, evaluations and/or programming as deemed appropriate by the COMPAS assessment and the probation agent.  Defendant must sign any releases agent deems necessary to verify defendant's compliance with probation conditions.  Not to enter into any bars, taverns, liquor stores, liquor department of grocery stores, the bar areas of restaurants. Defendant may not possess or consume any alcohol, nor be anywhere alcohol is available for consumption on the premises where the defendant is located.  Defendant must submit to random PBT's by probation agent or any law enforcement officer.  Must continue current AODA counseling/programming and comply all recommendations.  Must participate in and succesfully complete parenting classes or any other parenting skills programming available deemed appropriate by your agent.  Must maintain contact with social workers to get appropriate parenting classes.  Must check into Ho-Chunk Clan Mother's group and participate.  Must pay costs of the action.

Cooperate with the Dept. of Health and Human Services, obey social worker and child protection court orders.
